<?xml version='1.0' encoding='UTF-8'?>
<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1952-01-23T13:21:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1952-01-23T13:21:00-05:00" n="322" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d322">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">320/1–2352: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the United States Representative at the United Nations</hi>
                                (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Austin</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#left">
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                                <lb/>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">priority</hi>
                            </seg>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Paris</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1952-01-23T19:21:00+01:00">January
                                    23, 1952—7:21 p.m.</date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>
                            <gloss target="#t_Gadel2">Gadel</gloss> 813. Re Membership: <gloss target="#t_Dept1">Dept</gloss> was seriously concerned re letter
                            Guidotti considered sending other <gloss target="#t_SC1">SC</gloss>
                            members as reported <gloss target="#t_Delga1">Delga</gloss> 1128,<note n="1" xml:id="d322fn1">Not printed.</note> since letter wld have
                            given distorted impression re our position. <pb facs="0464" n="442" xml:id="pg_442"/> However, in view recent developments (<gloss target="#t_Delga1">Delga</gloss> 1148 and 1149), we assume Guidotti
                            now has no intention send such letter.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Acheson</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>